d%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJabalia%20was%20the%20biggest%20camp%20in%20the%20Palestinian%20territories%20before%20the%20war%2C%20which%20began%20after%20Hamas%20fighters%20attacked%20southern%20Israel%20on%20October%207%2C%20leaving%20some%201%2C160%20dead%2C%20based%20on%20Israeli%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGibril%2C%2060%2C%20fled%20there%20from%20nearby%20Beit%20Hanun%20when%20the%20conflict%20erupted.%20Home%20for%20him%20and%20his%20family%20is%20now%20a%20tent%20near%20what%20was%20a%20UN-run%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EContaminated%20water%2C%20power%20cuts%20and%20overcrowding%20were%20already%20a%20problem%20in%20the%20densely%20populated%20camp%2C%20which%20was%20set%20up%20in%201948%20and%20covers%20just%201.4%20square%20kilometres%20(half%20a%20square%20mile).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPoverty%2C%20from%20high%20unemployment%2C%20was%20also%20an%20issue%20among%20its%20more%20than%20100%2C000%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20food%20is%20running%20out%2C%20with%20aid%20agencies%20unable%20to%20get%20in%20to%20the%20area%20because%20of%20the%20bombing%20--%20and%20the%20frenzied%20looting%20of%20the%20few%20trucks%20that%20try%20to%20get%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20World%20Food%20Programme%20this%20week%20said%20its%20teams%20reported%20%26quot%3Bunprecedented%20levels%20of%20desperation%26quot%3B%20while%20the%20United%20Nations%20warned%20that%202.2%20million%20people%20were%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20famine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20the%20health%20ministry%20in%20Hamas-run%20Gaza%20said%20a%20two-month-old%20baby%20died%20of%20malnutrition%20in%20hospital%20in%20Gaza%20City%2C%20seven%20kilometres%20(just%20over%20four%20miles)%20away%20from%20Jabalia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20at%20least%2029%2C606%20people%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20Gaza%20in%20the%20war%2C%20the%20ministry%20said%20Saturday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScavenging%20and%20begging%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20camp%2C%20bedraggled%20children%20wait%20expectantly%2C%20holding%20plastic%20containers%20and%20battered%20cooking%20pots%20for%20what%20little%20food%20is%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20supplies%20dwindling%2C%20costs%20are%20rising.%20A%20kilo%20of%20rice%2C%20for%20example%2C%20has%20shot%20up%20from%20seven%20shekels%20(%241.90)%20to%2055%20shekels%2C%20complains%20one%20man.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20the%20grown-ups%20can%20still%20make%20it%20but%20these%20children%20who%20are%20four%20and%20five%20years%20old%2C%20what%20did%20they%20do%20wrong%20to%20sleep%20hungry%20and%20wake%20up%20hungry%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20angrily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UN%20children's%20agency%20UNICEF%20has%20warned%20that%20the%20alarming%20lack%20of%20food%2C%20surging%20malnutrition%20and%20disease%20could%20lead%20to%20an%20%26quot%3Bexplosion%26quot%3B%20in%20child%20deaths%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20in%20six%20children%20aged%20under%20two%20in%20Gaza%20was%20acutely%20malnourished%2C%20it%20estimated%20on%20February%2019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResidents%20have%20taken%20to%20eating%20scavenged%20scraps%20of%20rotten%20corn%2C%20animal%20fodder%20unfit%20for%20human%20consumption%20and%20even%20leaves%20to%20try%20to%20stave%20off%20the%20growing%20hunger%20pangs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20food%2C%20no%20wheat%2C%20no%20drinking%20water%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20woman.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20started%20begging%20neighbours%20for%20money.%20We%20don't%20have%20one%20shekel%20at%20home.%20We%20knock%20on%20doors%20and%20no%20one%20is%20giving%20us%20money%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E'Dying%20from%20hunger'%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETempers%20are%20rising%20in%20Jabalia%20about%20the%20lack%20of%20food%20and%20the%20consequences.%20On%20Friday%2C%20an%20impromptu%20protest%20was%20held%20involving%20dozens%20of%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20child%20held%20up%20a%20sign%20reading%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20didn't%20die%20from%20air%20strikes%20but%20we%20are%20dying%20from%20hunger.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20held%20aloft%20a%20placard%20warning%20%26quot%3BFamine%20eats%20away%20at%20our%20flesh%26quot%3B%2C%20while%20protesters%20chanted%20%26quot%3BNo%20to%20starvation.%20No%20to%20genocide.%20No%20to%20blockade.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Beit%20Hanun%2C%20Gibril%20used%20two%20horses%20to%20harvest%20a%20parcel%20of%20land.%20But%20the%20conflict%20destroyed%20that%2C%20along%20with%20his%20house%2C%20leaving%20him%20with%20nothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20weeks%20and%20months%2C%20Israel's%20relentless%20bombardment%20has%20left%20Gaza%20largely%20a%20place%20of%20shattered%20concrete%20and%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGibril%20kept%20the%20radical%20decision%20to%20slaughter%20his%20horses%20to%20himself%2C%20boiling%20the%20meat%20with%20rice%2C%20and%20giving%20it%20to%20his%20unwitting%20family%20and%20neighbours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20necessity%2C%20he%20said%20he%20was%20still%20wary%20of%20their%20reaction.%20%26quot%3BNo%20one%20knows%20they%20were%20in%20fact%20eating%20a%20horse.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708780440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2F6fg582us_gaza-refugee-camp-hunger-afp_625x300_24_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-hamas-war-didnt-die-from-air-strikes-dying-from-hunger-desperation-at-gaza-camp-5119308%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20the%20Jabalia%20refugee%20camp%20in%20northern%20Gaza%2C%20Abu%20Gibril%20was%20so%20desperate%20for%20food%20to%20feed%20his%20family%20that%20he%20slaughtered%20two%20of%20his%20horses.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-hamas-war-didnt-die-from-air-strikes-dying-from-hunger-desperation-at-gaza-camp-5119308%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-hamas-war-didnt-die-from-air-strikes-dying-from-hunger-desperation-at-gaza-camp-5119308%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fisrael-hamas-war-didnt-die-from-air-strikes-dying-from-hunger-desperation-at-gaza-camp-5119308%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%223%20newly-enacted%20criminal%20laws%20to%20come%20into%20effect%20from%20July%201%3A%20All%20you%20need%20to%20know%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708780075000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107970076%2Cimgsize-1062668.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fthree-newly-enacted-criminal-laws-to-come-into-effect-from-july-1-all-you-need-to-know%2Farticleshow%2F107970056.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Bharatiya%20Nyay%20Sanhita%2C%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%2C%20and%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Act%20will%20come%20into%20effect%20from%20July%201%2C%20replacing%20the%20British-era%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%2C%20and%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%20of%201872.%20The%20laws%20introduce%20definitions%20for%20terrorism%2C%20organized%20crime%2C%20and%20crimes%20against%20Women%20and%20Children.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fthree-newly-enacted-criminal-laws-to-come-into-effect-from-july-1-all-you-need-to-know%2Farticleshow%2F107970056.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ex%20Supreme%20Court%20Judge%20On%20Master%20Of%20Roster%20Business%20And%20Case%20Allocation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWading%20into%20a%20legal%20minefield%2C%20former%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20Kurian%20Joseph%20Saturday%20pitched%20for%20an%20expanded%20mechanism%20including%20at%20least%20three%20judges%20to%20decide%20allocation%20of%20cases%20in%20the%20apex%20court%20to%20end%20the%20public%20perception%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bmaster%20of%20roster%20business%26quot%3B%20is%20not%20being%20handled%20the%20way%20it%20should%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%20had%20in%20a%202018%20judgment%20said%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bmaster%20of%20the%20roster%26quot%3B%20and%20there%20is%20no%20dispute%20that%20he%20has%20the%20%26quot%3Bultimate%20authority%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bprerogative%26quot%3B%20to%20allocate%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20main%20observation%20I%20made%20after%20my%20retirement%20also%20is%20that%20there%20is%20a%20perception%20of%20a%20remote%20control%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20So%2C%20there%20is%20a%20perception%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20the%20public%20that%20the%20master%20of%20roster%20business%20is%20not%20handled%20the%20way%20it%20should%20be%20handled%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20my%20first%20suggestion%20on%20that%20master%20of%20roster%20business%20is%20that%20it%20should%20be%20done%20at%20least%20by%20three%20(judges)%2C%20and%20on%20the%20constitution%20of%20the%20benches%2C%20particularly%20very%20important%20constitutional%20matters%2C%20the%20diversity%20should%20be%20reflected%20--%20regional%2C%20gender%20--%20at%20least%20these%20two%20should%20be%20reflected%20in%20constituting%20the%20benches%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Joseph%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20one%20of%20the%20four%20most%20senior%20apex%20court%20judges%20who%20had%20held%20an%20unprecedented%20press%20conference%20in%20January%202018%20where%20they%20raised%20several%20issues%20including%20about%20assignment%20of%20cases%20in%20the%20top%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20at%20a%20seminar%20organised%20by%20the%20Campaign%20for%20Judicial%20Accountability%20and%20Reforms%20(CJAR)%2C%20Justice%20Joseph%20said%20after%20that%20press%20conference%2C%20a%20series%20of%20meetings%20of%20the%20incoming%20chief%20justices%20with%20the%20four%20judges%20took%20place%20and%20there%20was%20one%20suggestion%20that%20the%20master%20of%20roster%20exercise%20should%20be%20appropriately%20regulated%2C%20not%20controlled%2C%20in%20order%20to%20avoid%20any%20perceived%20arbitrariness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20apex%20court%20judge%20launched%20a%20frontal%20attack%20on%20the%20media%20for%20having%20failed%20to%20defend%20democracy%20and%20the%20Constitution%20as%20he%20made%20a%20spirited%20call%20for%20protecting%20whistle-blowers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20find%20any%20fearless%2C%20truthful%20version%20of%20the%20facts%20coming%20out.%20The%20greatest%20blow%20to%20democracy%20is%20that%20the%20fourth%20pillar%20has%20failed%20the%20country.%20Forget%20about%20the%20first%20three%20pillars.%20The%20fourth%20pillar%20is%20the%20media%20and%20they%20have%20failed%20to%20defend%20democracy.%20They%20have%20failed%20to%20defend%20the%20Constitution.%20They%20have%20failed%20to%20defend%20the%20truth%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20our%20only%20hope%20is%20the%20fifth%20pillar%2C%20whistle%20blowers.%20Somehow%20they%20are%20also%20not%20able%20to%20blow%2C%20maybe%20post%20COVID%20lungs%20have%20been%20affected.%20The%20way%20the%20lungs%20are%20crushed%20in%20the%20country%20today%20so%20that%20nobody%20will%20blow%20the%20whistle%20is%20a%20very%20dangerous%20trend%20for%20the%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20advised%20constitutional%20courts%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20equal%20importance%20has%20to%20be%20given%20to%20both%20aspects%20of%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution-life%20and%20liberty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20taking%20away%20the%20liberty%20part%20of%20a%20person%2C%20there%20is%20no%20point%20in%20giving%20him%20the%20life%20part.%20So%2C%20I%20think%2C%20I%20am%20of%20the%20strong%20view%20that%20our%20constitutional%20courts%20should%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20Article%2021%20should%20be%20understood%20giving%20equal%20importance%20to%20both%20aspects%20of%20life%20and%20liberty%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20the%20perception%20now%20is%20that%20life%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20guarded%20but%20liberty%20is%20ignored%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Joseph%20said%20while%20addressing%20the%20gathering%20at%20the%20first%20session%20of%20the%20seminar%20on%20'Supreme%20Court%20Administration%20and%20Management%3A%C2%93%20Issues%20and%20Concerns'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20Justice%20Joseph%2C%20former%20apex%20court%20judge%20Justice%20Madan%20B%20Lokur%2C%20former%20judge%20of%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20Justice%20Rekha%20Sharma%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Meenakshi%20Arora%2C%20and%20advocates%20Prashant%20Bhushan%20and%20Kamini%20Jaiswal%20also%20addressed%20the%20gathering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObserving%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20always%20been%20considered%20and%20conceived%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bguardian%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20he%20said%20judges%20take%20oath%20that%20they%20will%20uphold%20the%20Constitution%20and%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20seen%20judges%20speaking%20'I%20have%20done%20best%20according%20to%20my%20conscience'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20no%20special%20and%20individual%20conscience.%20His%20conscience%20is%20only%20the%20constitutional%20conscience.%20He%20is%20the%20conscience-keeper%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Joseph%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20trend%20now%20is%20if%20a%20case%20is%20posted%20to%20a%20bench%2C%20people%20are%20able%20to%20predict%20what%20the%20result%20would%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Joseph%20was%20elevated%20as%20a%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20March%208%2C%202013%20a