and%20problems%20of%20allocation%20of%20cases%20to%20benches%20by%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20who%20is%20regarded%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98master%20of%20roster%E2%80%99%2C%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Flatest%2F864783%2Fdemocracy-will-not-survive-if-problems-not-fixed-four-top-supreme-court-judges%5C%22%3Eunderlined%20at%20a%20press%20conference%20%3C%2Fa%3Eof%20the%20four%20senior%20most%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20January%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20the%20press%20conference%2C%20in%20which%20both%20Justice%20Joseph%20and%20Justice%20Madan%20Lokur%20had%20participated%2C%20along%20with%20Justices%20J.%20Chelameswar%2C%20Ranjan%20Gogoi%2C%20Justice%20Joseph%20said%20they%20held%20meetings%20for%20two%20weeks%20with%20incoming%20Chief%20Justices%20and%20came%20up%20with%20a%20suggestion%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmaster%20of%20roster%20exercise%20should%20be%20appropriately%20regulated%20to%20avoid%20perceived%20arbitrariness.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Joseph%20said%20that%20while%20he%20does%20not%20believe%20that%20any%20CJI%20is%20arbitrary%20but%20there%20may%20be%20a%20perception%20in%20the%20public.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20even%20perception%20of%20a%20remote%20control%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20had%20said%20the%20same%20at%20the%20time%20of%20his%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20suggested%20that%20the%20master%20of%20roster%20business%20should%20be%20dealt%20with%20by%20the%20first%20three%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20take%20a%20call%20on%C2%A0%20listing%20of%20cases%2C%20constitutional%20decorum%20subject%20allocation%20of%20cases%20and%20what%20to%20do%20in%20a%20case%20the%20judge%20recuses%20from%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20are%20the%20four%20situations%20in%20which%20the%20master%20of%20the%20roster%20has%20to%20act%20sensitively%20even%20though%20it%20has%20now%20become%20sensational.%20It%20is%20sensational%20because%20its%20constitutional%20sensitivity%20is%20not%20being%20considered%20the%20way%20it%20should%20be%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20constitution%20of%20benches%20on%20important%20constitutional%20matters%2C%20he%20suggested%2C%20%E2%80%9CRegional%20and%20gender%20diversity%20should%20be%20reflected.%E2%80%9D%20He%20added%20that%20nowadays%20the%20trend%20is%20that%20if%20a%20case%20is%20before%20a%20bench%2C%20%E2%80%9Cpeople%20are%20able%20to%20predict%20what%20the%20result%20is.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20speakers%20at%20the%20session%20included%20former%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20Justice%20Lokur%3B%20Justice%20Ajit%20Prakash%20Shah%2C%20former%20Chief%20Justice%2C%20Delhi%20high%20court%3B%20Justice%20Rekha%20Sharma%2C%20former%20judge%2C%20Delhi%20high%20court%3B%20Justice%20Govind%20Mathur%2C%20former%20Chief%20Justice%2C%20Allahabad%20high%20court%3B%20Kamini%20Jaiswal%2C%20advocate%2C%20Supreme%20Court%3B%20senior%20advocate%20Meenakshi%20Arora%3B%20advocate%20Gautam%20Bhatia%3B%20and%20Prashant%20Bhushan%2C%20advocate%20and%20convenor%2C%20Campaign%20for%20Judicial%20Accountability%20and%20Reforms%20(CJAR).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Frising-concerns-about-indias-judiciary%5C%22%3ERising%20Concerns%20About%20India%E2%80%99s%20Judiciary%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98When%20a%20case%20goes%20before%20a%20particular%20bench%2C%20this%20is%20going%20to%20be%20the%20result%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Lokur%20while%20agreeing%20with%20Justice%20Joseph%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CToday%2C%20the%20perception%20is%20that%20when%20the%20case%20goes%20before%20the%20particular%20bench%2C%20this%20is%20going%20to%20be%20the%20result.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20former%20JNU%20student%20and%20activist%20Umar%20Khalid%20w%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fumar-khalid-withdraws-bail-plea-in-supreme-court-citing-change-of-circumstances%5C%22%3Eithdrawing%20his%20bail%20plea%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%3C%2Fa%3Eearlier%20this%20month%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20Delhi%20riots%20larger%20conspiracy%20case%2C%20he%20said%20that%20it%20was%20done%20as%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20lawyer%20knew%20the%20fate%20of%20that%20case.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20have%20had%20the%20case%20of%20Umar%20Khalid%20asking%20for%20bail%2C%20which%20has%20not%20been%20listed%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20There%20have%20been%2013%20adjournments.%20Ultimately%2C%20the%20lawyer%20said%20that%20we%20wanted%20to%20withdraw%20the%20case%20because%20they%20knew%20what%20the%20result%20was%20going%20to%20be.%20They%20knew%20the%20fate%20of%20that%20case%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Lokur%20said%20that%20the%20first%20instance%2C%20according%20to%20him%2C%20when%20a%20chief%20justice%20exercised%20the%20power%20of%20the%20master%20of%20roster%20to%20change%20a%20bench%20was%20following%20the%20anti-Sikh%20riots%20in%201984.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20former%20Delhi%20high%20court%20Justice%20Rajinder%20Sachar%2C%20who%20wrote%20in%20his%20autobiography%20about%20the%20taking%20away%20of%20the%201984%20anti-Sikh%20riots%20case%20from%20his%20board%2C%20Justice%20Lokur%20said%20that%20during%20the%20course%20of%20the%20hearing%2C%20%E2%80%9Cit%20appeared%20that%20Justice%20Sachar%2C%20who%20was%20a%20great%20civil%20rights%20activist%2C%20was%20taking%20a%20particular%20view%20which%20was%20not%20helpful%20to%20the%20government.%20This%20was%20sometime%20in%20December.%20After%20the%20court%20vacations%20were%20over%2C%20in%20January%2C%20Justice%20Sachar%20found%20that%20the%20case%20had%20been%20taken%20away%20from%20his%20Board.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20took%20it%20up%20with%20the%20Chief%20Justice%2C%20but%20nothing%20happened%E2%80%A6That%20was%20as%20far%20as%20I%20know%20the%20first%20documented%20case%20of%20a%20Chief%20Justice%20exercising%20the%20power%20of%20master%20of%20roster%20to%20list%20a%20case%20before%20a%20particular%20bench%20or%20to%20take%20it%20out%20of%20a%20particular%20bench%20so%20that%20an%20order%20which%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20did%20not%20want%20could%20not%20be%20passed%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Justice%20Lokur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20the%20cases%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-arnab-goswami-bail-hearing%5C%22%3EArnab%20Goswami%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-sets-aside-bombay-hc-order-discharging-g-n-saibaba-in-maoist-links-case%5C%22%3EG.N.%20Saibaba%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20underlined%20that%20the%20issue%20is%20when%20a%20matter%20is%20listed%20and%20where.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20would%20have%20a%20situation%20where%20somebody%2C%20a%20journalist%2C%20wants%20bail%2C%20the%20case%20is%20listed%20the%20same%20day%20maybe%20in%20the%20evening%E2%80%A6somebody%20has%20been%20granted%20bail%2C%20the%20prosecution%20says%20grant%20of%20bail%20by%20the%20High%20Court%20is%20wrong%E2%80%A6so%20a%20special%20bench%20sits%20on%20a%20Saturday%20and%20stays%20that%20order%2C%20which%20is%20very%20very%20unusual%2C%20so%20that%20the%20person%20does%20not%20come%20out%20of%20jail.%20Why%20should%20that%20happen%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20contrasted%20the%20cases%20with%20Khalid%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20Article%20370%20case%20and%20electoral%20bonds%20case%20that%20were%20not%20listed%20for%20years.%20Offering%20two%20solutions%2C%20Justice%20Lokur%20said%20that%20one%20could%20be%20to%20pass%20on%20the%20message%20so%20%E2%80%9Ccorrective%20steps%20are%20taken.%E2%80%9D%20The%20other%20solution%2C%20which%20he%20referred%20to%20as%20more%20%E2%80%9Cfearsome%E2%80%9D%20was%20Parliament%20enacting%20a%20legislation%20on%20how%20the%20apex%20court%20should%20function.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20had%20that%20example%20very%20recently%20in%20the%20appointment%20of%20election%20commissioners%20when%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20gave%20a%20direction%20and%C2%A0%20the%20parliament%20made%20a%20law%20and%20removed%20the%20CJI%20and%20included%20a%20cabinet%20minister%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLawmaking%20is%20a%20solution%2C%20but%20it%20is%20a%20very%20fearsome%20and%20fearful%20solution%20that%20is%20available%20under%20the%20constitution.%20Before%20that%20happens%2C%20I%20think%2C%20we%20need%20to%20get%20our%20act%20together%20and%20ensure%20that%20there%20is%20justice%20in%20listing%20both%20in%20time%20and%20benches%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Lokur%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-supreme-court-never-fails-to-disappoint%5C%22%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20Never%20Fails%20to%20Disappoint%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Who%20assigns%20the%20case%20and%20who%20decides%20the%20matter%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Delhi%20high%20court%20judge%20Justice%20Rekha%20Sharma%20said%20that%20the%20question%20is%20not%20just%20about%20the%20roster%20of%20judges%2C%20but%20%E2%80%9Cwho%20assigns%20the%20case%20and%20who%20decides%20the%20matter%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20apparent%20reference%20to%20former%20Chief%20Justice%20Ranjan%20Gogoi%2C%20who%20led%20the%20five-judge%20constitution%20bench%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fayodhya-verdict-supreme-court-full-text%5C%22%3EAyodhya%20title%20dispute%20case%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20subsequently%20was%20appointed%20to%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20Justice%20Sharma%20said%20there%20are%20three%20pronounced%20advantages%20of%20the%20roster%20system%20which%20%E2%80%9Cfortunately%20or%20unfortunately%20have%20become%20public.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNumber%20one%2C%20the%20master%20of%20the%20roster%20can%20constitute%20a%20bench%20of%20his%20own%20choice%20and%20himself%20preside%20over%20it%20even%20in%20the%20very%20personal%20matter.%20Number%20two%2C%20by%20intelligently%20making%20use%20of%20that%20power%2C%20he%20can%20assure%20himself%20even%20after%20his%20retirement%2C%20a%20cosy%20job%20like%20a%20seat%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%20or%20governorship%20in%20some%20state.%20Number%20three%2C%20by%20intelligently%20using%20his%20power%20he%20can%20equally%20benefit%20his%20very%20worthy%20and%20dearest%20colleagues%20too%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Loss%20of%20public%20confidence%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocate%20Meenakshi%20Arora%20said%20that%20a%20case%20like%20Khalid%E2%80%99s%20being%20withdrawn%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20shows%20a%20%E2%80%9Closs%20of%20public%20confidence%20in%20an%20institution%20altogether.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArora%20said%20justice%20has%20to%20be%20uniform%20and%20in%20criminal%20cases%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20declare%20which%20criminal%20bench%20is%20likely%20to%20hear%20which%20category%20of%20cases-whether%20death%20penalty%2C%20economic%20offences%20or%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COnce%20you%20have%20done%20that%20the%20earmarking%20of%20cases%20should%20be%20by%20automation%20and%20no%20hand%20must%20come%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArora%20said%20there%20mechanisms%20should%20be%20brought%20to%20regulate%20the%20office%20of%20the%20master%20of%20the%20roster.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20master%20of%20the%20roster%20today%20is%20unregulated%20and%20requires%20much%20more%20transparency%20and%20accountability%20for%20the%20acts%20that%20are%20being%20done%20by%20that%20high%20office.%20There%20is%20no%20grievance%20redressal%20mechanism%20of%20the%20working%20of%20the%20master%20of%20roster.%20This%20office%20is%20more%20inclined%20towards%20the%20rule%20of%20a%20man%20than%20rule%20of%20law.%20We%20are%20reposing%20this%20power%20to%20one%20individual%20to%20which%20there%20is%20no%20check%20and%20balance%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaiswal%20said%20that%20the%20most%20concerning%20issue%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpost%20retirement%20jobs%E2%80%9D%20being%20given%20to%20judges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20find%20them%20working%20very%20well%20till%20they%20reach%20the%20top.%20When%20they%20reach%20near%20retirement%2C%20they%20turn%20into%20a%20new%20cover%2C%20which%20is%20not%20a%20nice%20cover.%20The%20question%20of%20constitution%20and%20listing%20of%20cases%20must%20have%20guidelines%2C%20roster%20system%20works%20as%20per%20subject.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20once%20a%20roster%20is%20made%20the%20chief%20justice%20should%20have%20any%20say%20in%20transferring%20from%20one%20bench%20to%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20in%20super%20sensitive%20matters%20of%20national%20importance%2C%20%E2%80%9Cit%20is%20necessary%20that%20the%20decision%20cannot%20be%20left%20to%20one%20individual.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20has%20to%20be%20done%20by%20at%20least%20three%20senior-most%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%20court%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20speech%2C%20Bhushan%20pointed%20out%20that%20recent%20judgments%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20the%20electoral%20bond%20case%20and%20Chandigarh%20mayor%20election%20case%20has%20rekindled%20hope%20in%20the%20apex%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20reiterated%2C%20citing%20a%20petition%20filed%20by%20Shanti%20Bhushan%20in%202018%2C%20that%20was%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fcji-is-the-master-of-roster-sc-dismisses-shanti-bhushans-petition%2F%5C%22%3E%20dismissed%20by%20the%20apex%20court%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20said%20the%20master%20of%20roster%20system%20should%20not%20be%20with%20one%20individual%20but%20five%20senior-most%20judges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20former%20CJI%20Ranjan%20Gogoi%2C%20who%20was%20part%20of%20the%20bench%20that%20heard%20a%20sexual%20harassment%20case%20against%20him%2C%20Bhushan%20said%20the%20master%20of%20roster%20%E2%80%9Ccan%20be%20abused%20arbitrarily.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThat%20shows%20how%20this%20power%20of%20the%20master%20of%20the%20roster%20can%20be%20abused%20so%20arbitrarily%20and%20sometimes%20for%20their%20own%20cause.%20Often%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20government%20or%20the%20state%20or%20sometimes%20for%20their%20own%20cause%20if%20they%20choose%20to%20do%20so%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708777823000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fperception-of-remote-control-in-sc-former-judges-advocates-on-master-of-roster-and-arbitrariness%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'Today%2C%20the%20perception%20is%20that%20when%20the%20case%20goes%20before%20the%20particular%20bench%2C%20this%20is%20going%20to%20be%20the%20result%2C'%20Justice%20Lokur%20said%2C%20while%20speaking%20at%20a%20seminar%20organised%20by%20the%20Campaign%20for%20Judicial%20Accountability%20and%20Reforms%2C%20in%20collaboration%20with%20'The%20Wire'%20and%20'LiveLaw'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fperception-of-remote-control-in-sc-former-judges-advocates-on-master-of-roster-and-arbitrariness%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Haldwani%20violence%20key%20accused%20Abdul%20Malik%20arrested%20in%20Delhi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708777275000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107969512%2Cimgsize-850184.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Futtarakhand-police-arrests-key-accused-in-haldwani-violence%2Farticleshow%2F107969237.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%