bha-polls-next-week-pm-may-be-on-it-sources-5119020%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbjp-to-release-list-of-100-candidates-for-lok-sabha-polls-next-week-pm-may-be-on-it-sources-5119020%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Lt%20Governor%20Writes%20To%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%2C%20Questions%20%26quot%3BStalling%20Of%20Budget%26quot%3B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EOpening%20another%20front%20in%20his%20battle%20with%20the%20AAP%2C%20the%20Delhi%20lieutenant%20governor%20has%20written%20to%20Chief%20Minister%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20and%20questioned%20the%20delay%20in%20presenting%20the%20budget.%20Hitting%20out%20at%20the%20government%2C%20LG%20VK%20Saxena%20has%20accused%20it%20of%20%26quot%3Bstalling%20the%20budget%20for%20no%20apparent%20reason%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20the%20people%20have%20a%20right%20to%20know%20how%20public%20funds%20are%20being%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaturday's%20letter%20by%20the%20LG%20comes%20a%20day%20after%20his%20missive%20to%20Mr%20Kejriwal%20regarding%20five%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20reports%20that%2C%20he%20said%2C%20have%20been%20%26quot%3Bpending%26quot%3B%20with%20Delhi%20Finance%20Minister%20Atishi%20since%20August%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2015%2C%20the%20budget%20session%20of%20the%20Assembly%20had%20been%20extended%20till%20the%20first%20week%20of%20March%20after%20Ms%20Atishi%20had%20said%20in%20the%20House%20that%20there%20had%20been%20some%20delays%20in%20the%20finalisation%20of%20the%20financial%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Saturday's%20letter%2C%20Mr%20Saxena%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20constrained%20to%20bring%20to%20your%20notice%20that%20despite%20the%20Annual%20Financial%20Statement%20being%20ready%20and%20available%20with%20the%20Government%2C%20after%20due%20clearance%20of%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20since%20as%20long%20as%2019.02.2024%2C%20it%20is%20yet%20to%20reach%20me%20for%20causing%20it%20to%20be%20laid%20in%20the%20House%20as%20per%20law%20established.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPointing%20out%20that%20the%20Centre%20had%20approved%20the%20budget%20on%20February%2019%2C%20three%20days%20after%20the%20Delhi%20government%20had%20sent%20it%2C%20the%20LG%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThereafter%2C%20the%20process%20seems%20to%20have%20been%20stalled%20for%20no%20apparent%20reason%20at%20the%20level%20of%20GNCTD%20(Government%20of%20National%20Capital%20Territory%20of%20Delhi)...%20it%20will%20be%20in%20the%20fitness%20of%20things%20that%20the%20Annual%20Financial%20Statement%20(Budget)%2C%20be%20laid%2C%20discussed%20and%20passed%20in%20the%20Assembly%20at%20the%20earliest%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20people%20of%20Delhi.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDoing%20so%2C%20Mr%20Saxena%20wrote%2C%20will%20give%20the%20people%20of%20Delhi%20an%20opportunity%20to%20know%20the%20expenses%20and%20revenue%20of%20the%20government%20and%20also%20find%20out%20what%20the%20public%20funds%2C%20which%20%26quot%3Bbelong%20to%20the%20people%20themselves%26quot%3B%2C%20are%20being%20utilised%20for.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20are%20accordingly%20requested%20to%20get%20the%20process%20expedited%20and%20utilise%20the%20Budget%20Session%20for%20what%20it%20was%20summoned%20for%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20transparency%2C%20accountability%20and%20good%20governance%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20signed%20off.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPending%20Reports%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20letter%20to%20the%20chief%20minister%20on%20Friday%2C%20Mr%20Saxena%20had%20requested%20him%20to%20ask%20the%20Delhi%20finance%20minister%20to%20%26quot%3Bexpeditiously%20process%26quot%3B%20five%20reports%20by%20the%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20(CAG)%20so%20they%20could%20be%20tabled%20in%20the%20ongoing%20budget%20session.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStating%20that%20the%20reports%20of%20the%20CAG%20are%20a%20constitutionally%20mandated%20independent%20and%20impartial%20assessment%20of%20the%20perfor