tle%20suggests%2C%20%3Cem%3EInsides%20and%20Outsides%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20about%20two%20worlds%3A%20the%20household%20and%20the%20country%3B%20the%20family%20and%20the%20society.%20Ahmad%20finds%20himself%20awkwardly%20lodged%20between%20these%20poles%2C%20discovering%20and%20rediscovering%20his%20own%20self%20%E2%80%93%20and%20identity%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20does%20it%20mean%20to%20be%20a%20Muslim%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20India%3F%20The%20film%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20offer%20a%20conclusive%20answer%2C%20perhaps%20because%20there%20is%20none.%20So%2C%20with%20sombre%20honesty%20and%20humility%2C%20it%20merely%20attempts%20to%20answer%20that%20question%20through%20personal%20ethnography.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENowhere%20does%20%3Cem%3EInsides%20and%20Outsides%20%3C%2Fem%3Eassume%20that%20every%20Muslim%20person%20or%20family%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20India%20would%20feel%20the%20same%20way%20about%20the%20pandemonium%20around%20them%20as%20Arbab%20and%20his%20parents%20do.%20Yet%2C%20there%20is%20a%20profound%20universality%20in%20their%20story%20that%20is%20hard%20to%20dismiss.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20film%2C%20Ahmad%20uses%20two%20voices%20when%20he%20talks%20about%20himself%20or%20his%20feelings%20%E2%80%93%20first%20and%20third%20person.%20When%20he%20uses%20the%20latter%2C%20he%20refers%20to%20himself%20by%20name%2C%20as%20if%20in%20an%20out-of-body%20experience.%20One%20may%20see%20this%20astral%20projection%20as%20a%20metaphor%20for%20the%20Muslim%20self%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20India%20that%20often%20finds%20itself%20questioning%20its%20own%20identity%2C%20choices%20and%20ideologies%20from%20a%20distance.%20This%20internal%20fracturing%20of%20the%20Muslim%20self%20is%20perhaps%20one%20of%20the%20most%20severe%20repercussions%20of%20the%20majoritarian%20onslaught%20that%20the%20community%20is%20being%20subjected%20to%20in%20India%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EInsides%20and%20Outsides%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20able%20to%20effortlessly%20oscillate%20between%20the%20home%20and%20the%20world%2C%20the%20mundane%20and%20the%20extraordinary%2C%20precisely%20because%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20pretend%20to%20be%20something%20it%20isn%E2%80%99t%20%E2%80%93%20a%20grand%20ideological%20treatise%20about%20%3Cem%3EMuslim-ness%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20a%20Hindu%20majoritarian%20India.%20So%2C%20it%20is%20able%20to%20uncompromisingly%20talk%20about%20the%20politics%20of%20majoritarian%20violence%20in%20the%20country%20and%20the%20nonchalance%20of%20daily%20life%20in%20a%20middle-class%20Muslim%20household%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20The%20political%20and%20the%20personal%20melt%20into%20each%20other%20without%20one%20completely%20diluting%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20key%20motif%20in%20Ahmad%E2%80%99s%20story%20is%3A%20movement.%20He%20consciously%20dwells%20on%20it%20through%20the%20film%20using%20the%20dual%20pivots%20of%20space%20and%20time.%20Muslims%20in%20India%20have%20always%20been%20on%20the%20move%20since%20the%20Partition.%20They%20continue%20to%20be%20so%20even%20today%20%E2%80%93%20not%20because%20they%20want%20to%2C%20but%20because%20they%20are%20forced%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhmad%20himself%20is%20moving%20houses%2C%20as%20his%20father%20retires%20from%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Technology%2C%20Delhi%20after%2041%20years%20in%20service%20as%20a%20professor.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20has%20arrived%2C%20bringing%20along%20even%20more%20uncertainty%2C%20worry%20and%20prejudice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEverything%20is%20restive%2C%20nothing%20is%20the%20same%20anymore%20%E2%80%93%20from%20their%20house%20to%20the%20world%20around%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20perhaps%2C%20the%20strongest%20motif%20in%20%3Cem%3EInsides%20and%20Outsides%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%3A%20resilience.%20Ahmad%E2%80%99s%20mother%20talks%20about%20sectarian%20violence%2C%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20the%20steady%20unravelling%20of%20the%20culture%20of%20respect%20while%20cooking%20biryani%20and%20admonishing%20her%20husband%20for%20driving%20too%20fast.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20frame%2C%20his%20father%20directs%20his%20son%20to%20move%20the%20camera%20away%20from%20him%20and%20instead%2C%20film%20the%20posing%20peacock%20in%20the%20lawn%2C%20and%20in%20the%20next%20frame%2C%20he%20is%20seen%20shuffling%20through%20old%20files%20to%20ascertain%20which%20of%20his%20documents%20would%20stand%20the%20National%20Register%20of%20Citizens%E2%80%99%20(NRC)%20test.%20The%20contradictions%20chill%20the%20spine%2C%20but%20their%20infectious%20smiles%2C%20visible%20in%20nearly%20every%20frame%2C%20warm%20the%20heart.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhmad%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20seamlessly%20merge%20images%20and%20sounds%20is%20conspicuous%20throughout%20the%20film.%20In%20one%20scene%2C%20he%20is%20seen%20reading%20out%20the%20case%20details%20of%20various%20Muslim%20individuals%20who%20were%20lynched%20by%20Hindu%20mobs%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%20for%20allegedly%20carrying%20beef%20or%20the%20COVID-19%20pathogen.%20As%20he%20does%20that%2C%20Ahmad%E2%80%99s%20mother%20knocks%20at%20the%20door%20and%20calls%20him%20out%20%E2%80%93%20the%20din%20growing%20louder%20and%20more%20frantic%20by%20the%20second.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fzeherkhurani-nirmala-bhuradias-latest-novel-holds-mirror-to-our-times-consumed-by-hate%5C%22%3EZeherkhurani%E2%80%99%3A%20Nirmala%20Bhuradia%E2%80%99s%20Latest%20Novel%20Holds%20a%20Mirror%20to%20Our%20Times%20Consumed%20by%20Hate%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20juxtaposition%20of%20his%20factual%20recitation%20and%20his%20mother%E2%80%99s%20desperate%20knocks%20ends%20up%20creating%20a%20harrowing%20sense%20of%20anxiety%20and%20claustrophobia.%20It%20is%20as%20if%20the%20walls%20around%20Ahmad%20were%20rapidly%20closing%20in%20on%20him.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20he%20ends%20up%20conjuring%20a%20profound%20audio-visual%20metaphor%20for%20the%20plight%20of%20an%20average%20Indian%20Muslim%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhmad%20is%20also%20sharply%20aware%20of%20his%20own%20class%20privileges%20as%20a%20Muslim%20born%20into%20a%20well-off%20family%2C%20protected%20by%20a%20certain%20degree%20of%20generational%20security.%20He%20understands%20that%20Muslims%20from%20economically%20marginalised%20backgrounds%20face%20greater%20risks%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20India%20%E2%80%93%20a%20point%20that%20becomes%20clear%20when%20he%20explains%20to%20his%20mother%2C%20as%20they%20stand%20on%20a%20foot%20over%20bridge%20atop%20the%20erstwhile%20protest%20site%20at%20Shaheen%20Bagh%2C%20why%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20interview%20some%20of%20the%20locals%20on%20camera.%20Shaheen%20Bagh%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20is%20yet%20another%20recurring%20motif%20in%20the%20film%2C%20both%20as%20a%20Muslim%20ghetto%20and%20a%20site%20of%20righteous%20resistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EInsides%20and%20Outsides%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20not%20an%20ideological%20manifesto.%20It%20is%2C%20rather%2C%20a%20deeply%20personal%20diary%20of%20a%20pensive%2C%20perplexed%20and%20perturbed%20self%20that%20today%20finds%20itself%20dangling%20between%20two%20different%20worlds%3B%20a%20collection%2C%20even%2C%20of%20intimate%20thoughts%20jotted%20hurriedly%20on%20small%20pieces%20of%20paper%3B%20as%20assortment%20of%2C%20as%20Ahmad%20himself%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9Cdrafts%20on%20moving%E2%80%9D.%20Yet%2C%20it%20is%20also%20a%20tender%20story%20of%20bearing%20witness%20to%20political%20tumult%2C%20and%20of%20seeking%20refuge%20in%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20must%20thank%20Ahmad%20for%20letting%20us%20bear%20witness%20alongside%20him%2C%20for%20generously%20opening%20the%20doors%20of%20his%20home%20for%20us%2C%20and%20for%20telling%20a%20story%20that%20needed%20to%20be%20told.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAngshuman%20Choudhury%20is%20an%20associate%20fellow%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20Policy%20Research%2C%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708776052000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F24135539%2FScreen-Shot-2024-02-24-at-1.55.04-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Finsides-and-outsides-arbab-ahmads-documentary-is-a-tender-tale-of-bearing-witness%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20the%20title%20suggests%2C%20'Insides%20and%20Outsides'%20is%20about%20two%20worlds%3A%20the%20household%20and%20the%20country%3B%20the%20family%20and%20the%20society.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Finsides-and-outsides-arbab-ahmads-documentary-is-a-tender-tale-of-bearing-witness%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22PM%20Modi%20shares%20a%20throwback%20video%20ahead%20of%20Rajkot%20visit%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708776004000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107968986%2Cimgsize-509770.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fpm-modi-shares-throwback-video-of-his-first-electoral-win-ahead-of-rajkot-visit%2Farticleshow%2F107968575.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fpm-modi-shares-throwback-video-of-his-first-electoral-win-ahead-of-rajkot-visit%2Farticleshow%2F107968575.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Putin%20Critic%20May%20Have%20Been%20Killed%20With%20%26quot%3BSingle%20Punch%20To%20Heart%26quot%3B%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERussian%20opposition%20leader%20Alexei%20Navalny%20may%20have%20been%20killed%20with%20a%20single%20punch%20to%20the%20heart%20-%20an%20old%20method%20used%20by%20the%20KGB%20-%20a%20human%20rights%20activist%20has%20claimed.%20This%20comes%20even%20as%20the%20Russian%20officials%20are%20yet%20to%20release%20Navalny's%20body%20who%20died%20suddenly%20a%20week%20ago%20in%20the%20Arctic%20penal%20colony%20where%20he%20had%20been%20serving%20sentences%20totalling%20more%20than%2030%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20an%20old%20method%20of%20the%20KGB's%20special%20forces%20divisions%2C%26quot%3B%20Vladimir%20Osechkin%2C%20founder%20of%20the%20human%20rights%20group%20Gulagu.net%2C%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thetimes.co.uk%2Farticle%2Falexei-navalny-killed-punch-death-cause-russia-putin-x86g6jcdx%5C%22%3ETimes%20of%20London%20%3C%2Fa%3Eciting%20a%20source%20at%20the%20penal%20colony.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20trained%20their%20operatives%20to%20kill%20a%20man%20with%20one%20punch%20in%20the%20heart%2C%20in%20the%20center%20of%20the%20body.%20It%20was%20a%20hallmark%20of%20the%20KGB%2C%26quot%3B%20Osechkin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKGB%20was%20much-feared%20Soviet-era%20internal%20security%20service.%20It%20was%20officially%20dissolved%20on%20December%203%2C%201991.%20It%20was%20later%20succeeded%20in%20Russia%20by%20the%20Foreign%20Intelligence%20Service%20(SVR)%20and%20what%20would%20later%20become%20the%20Federal%20Security%20Service%20(FSB).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20claimed%20that%20ahead%20of%20the%20fatal%20strike%2C%20the%2047-year-old%20had%20been%20kept%20outdoors%20for%20hours%20in%20the%20harsh%2C%20subzero%20temperatures%20to%20weaken%20his%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20they%20first%20destroyed%20his%20body%20by%20keeping%20him%20out%20in%20the%20cold%20for%20a%20long%20time%20and%20slowing%20the%20blood%20circulation%20down%20to%20a%20minimum%2C%26quot%3B%20Osechkin%20said%2C%20citinig%20an%20unidentified%20source%20working%20at%20the%20prison.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20it%20becomes%20very%20easy%20to%20kill%20someone%2C%20within%20seconds%2C%20if%20the%20operative%20has%20some%20experience%20in%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20a%20report%2C%20the%20body%20of%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20most%20vociferous%20critic%20had%20%26quot%3Bsigns%20of%20bruises%26quot%3B%2C%20an%20anonymours%20paramedic%20told%20an%20independent%20news%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20paramedic%20said%20the%20bodies%20of%20those%20who%20die%20in%20prison%20are%20usually%20taken%20straight%20to%20the%20Foreign%20Medicine%20Bureau%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20his%20body%20was%20taken%20to%20a%20clinical%20hospital%20for%20some%20reason.%26quot%3B%20The%20%26quot%3Bbruises%26quot%3B%20on%20his%20body%20resembled%20marks%20that%20one%20suffers%20when%20being%20held%20down%20during%20a%20seizure%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlexei%20Navalny's%20team%20has%20claimed%20that%20Russian%20authorities%20have%20told%20his%20mother%20he%20would%20be%20buried%20in%20the%20penal%20colony%20unless%20she%20agreed%20to%20lay%20him%20to%20rest%20without%20a%20public%20funeral.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny's%20mother%20Lyudmila%20has%20been%20demanding%20for%20days%20that%20authorities%20hand%20over%20his%20body%20to%20be%20buried%20in%20a%20way%20that%20will%20allow%20his%20friends%2C%20family%20and%20supporters%20to%20pay%20their%20respects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny's%20family%20and%20supporters%20have%20accused%20Putin%20of%20having%20him%20killed%2C%20an%20accusation%20that%20the%20Kremlin%20has%20angrily%20rejected.%20He%20had%20survived%20a%20poisoning%20attempt%20in%202020%20and%20years%20of%20harsh%20treatment%20in%20prison%2C%20including%20long%20spells%20in%20solitary%20confinement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPutin%2C%20who%20never%20mentioned%20Navalny%20in%20his%20speeches%2C%20has%20not%20yet%20commented%20on%20his%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYulia%20Navalnaya%2C%20the%20widow%20of%20Navalny%2C%20has%20released%20a%20six-minute%20video%20on%20Saturday%20and%20demanded%20that%20Russian%20authorities%20release%20his%20body%20for%20burial%20and%20accused%20a%20%26quot%3Bdemonic%26quot%3B%20Putin%20of%20%26quot%3Btorturing%26quot%3B%20his%20corpse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Russian%20officials%2C%20Navalny%20%26quot%3Bfely%20unwell%20after%20a%20walk%2C%20almost%20immediately%20losing%20consciousness%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BAll%20necessary%20resuscitation%20measures%20were%20carried%20out%2C%20which%20did%20not%20give%20positive%20results.%20Doctors%20of%20the%20ambulance%20stated%20the%20death%20of%20the%20convict.%20The%20causes%20of%20death%20are%20being%20established%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20mother%20was%20given%20a%20notice%20of%20the%20death%20that%20had%202.17%20pm%20local%20time%20(2.37%20pm%20IST)%20on%20February%2016.%20She%20was%20told%20the%20cause%20of%20his%20death%20was%20%26quot%3Bsudden%20death%20syndrome%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSudden%20death%20syndrome%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20vague%20term%20for%20different%20cardiac%20syndromes%20that%20cause%20sudden%20cardiac%20arrest%20and%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708775520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fi21k9img_alexei-navalny_625x300_16_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fputin-critic-alexei-navalny-may-have-been-killed-with-single-punch-to-heart-claims-activist-vladimir-osechkin-5119199%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russian%20opposition%20leader%20Alexei%20Navalny%20may%20have%20been%20killed%20with%20a%20single%20punch%20to%20the%20heart%20-%20an%20old%20method%20used%20by%20the%20KGB%20-%20a%20human%20rights%20activist%20has%20claimed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fputin-critic-alexei-navalny-may-have-been-killed-with-single-punch-to-heart-claims-activist-vladimir-osechkin-5119199%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fputin-critic-alexei-navalny-may-have-been-killed-with-single-punch-to-heart-claims-activist-vladimir-osechkin-5119199%2Famp%2F1%2