0government%20has%20not%20paid%20dues%20for%20the%20last%20two%20years%20and%20a%20number%20of%20private%20and%20trust-run%20hospitals%20are%20%E2%80%9Con%20the%20verge%20of%20bankruptcy%E2%80%9D.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fahmedabad%2Fdues-pending-hospitals-wont-accept-pmjay-patients-from-february-26-29-9176165%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20that%20Association%20also%20claimed%20that%20multiple%20representations%20to%20the%20government%20officials%2C%20including%20the%20Union%20health%20minister%20Mansukh%20Mandaviya%2C%20went%20unheard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFollowing%20the%20press%20conference%2C%20we%20received%20a%20call%20from%20the%20office%20of%20Gujarat%20Health%20Minister%20Rushikesh%20Patel%20for%20a%20meeting%20on%20February%2021.%20We%20met%20Principal%20Secretary%20(Health)%20Dhananjay%20Dwivedi%20and%20other%20officials%20but%20they%20only%20orally%20assured%20us%20that%20our%20issues%20will%20be%20resolved%20and%20refused%20to%20give%20us%20anything%20in%20writing%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20association%E2%80%99s%20media%20spokesperson%20Dr%20Ramesh%20Chaudhary%20told%20the%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20proceed%20with%20our%20symbolic%20protest.%20The%20hospitals%20have%20decided%20not%20to%20accept%20any%20patient%20under%20PMJAY%20from%20February%2026%20to%2029.%20If%20our%20issues%20remain%20unresolved%20even%20after%20that%2C%20we%20may%20proceed%20to%20not%20accept%20patients%20under%20PMJAY%20indefinitely%20and%20intensify%20our%20movement%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20The%20Association%20also%20complained%20about%20%E2%80%9Cunexplained%20deductions%20and%20rejection%20of%20claims%20by%20the%20insurance%20company%20Bajaj%20Allianz%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708775053000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F04140813%2F6872410817_7beee43941_b.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3